name: Aberdeen FC - COYR Beanie 'Home Colours'
description:
The 'COYR' slouchy beanie - 2013 Edition.

White embroidery of distressed type - COYR on a red hat, to compliment Aberdeen FC's home colours. These are part of the second edition of COYR beanies, and are also available in different colour combinations. 

One size fits all slouchy beanie.

name: Aberdeen FC - COYR Beanie 'Away Colours'
description:
The 'COYR' slouchy beanie - 2013 Edition.

Distressed typography of red embroidery of COYR on a black hat, to compliment Aberdeen FC's away colours. These are part of the second edition of COYR beanies, and are also available in different colour combinations. 

One size fits all slouchy beanie.

name: Aberdeen FC - COYR Beanie 'Vintage'
description:
The 'COYR' slouchy beanie - 2013 Edition.

Distressed typography on gold embroidery of COYR on a black hat, to compliment Aberdeen FC's historical colours. These are part of the second edition of COYR beanies, and are also available in different colour combinations.

name: Aberdeen FC - V is for Victory - Beanie
description:
An old skool beanie. Inspired by the 1970s 'V is for Victory' patch design. We've erm, created a patch and sewn on to a traditional granite grey beanie. 

Crafted just like yer Ma would've pre-1976 League Cup Final.

options.name: The Northern White of Old Aberdeen

name: Aberdeen FC - Willie/Che Beanie
description:
Another collab with Dons supporting designer Rich. This time his Willie/Che design has been embroidered onto a patch and stitched on to a traditional granite grey beanie.

Image displayed is a mock up...

options.name: The Northern White of Old Aberdeen

name: Aberdeen FC - 1903 Traditional Beanie 'Pink'
description:
Introducing the 'Traditional Beanie' to our range of Dolly Digital headwear.

Last year our 'COYR Slouchy Beanies' were extremely popular, but we had a few requests for a more traditional beanie. So we've listened to you and this year we're pleased to announce the release of the '1903 Trad Beanie'.

We don't want to sound stereotypical, but we have had requests from female fans for items to be produced in pink. Again we've listened so this is the first...

RED embroidery of 1903 on a traditional PINK beanie. These are part of the first edition of 1903 beanies, which will also be available in different colourways.

One size fits all beanie.

name: Aberdeen FC - Bucket Hat: Sheep
description:
The two-tone bucket hat. Synonymous with Hampden trips in the sunshine or under the floodlights.

We've collaborated with Gordon Reid, illustrator extraordinaire. Gordon is best know for his caricatures of all things Aberdeen. His art adorns the pages of The Red Final (The Northern Light before that), the stairways to the RDU, The Pittodrie Bar and now our bucket hats!

The 'Stand Free Sheep' is positioned centrally on the hat and is screen printed, by hand in three colours. 

Perfect for fitba and festivals...

Designed in Aberdeen. Screen-printed by hand in Aberdeen. This hat IS Aberdeen.

name: Aberdeen FC - Bucket Hat: COYR Special
description:
Two-tone bucket hat, synonymous with Hampden trips in sunshine or under the floodlights. We've tried to stay authentic to the original cut of the 80s and 90s bucket hats. But we've put our own spin on the design. Others have likened it to 'Ska' culture, or more specifically 'Two Tone'. We'll accept this compliment so it's named the 'COYR Special'.

Screen printed check with off-centre 'COYR'.

Perfect for fitba and festivals...

Designed in Aberdeen. Screen-printed by hand in Aberdeen. This hat IS Aberdeen.

name: Aberdeen FC - Bucket Hat: Retro
description:
This much anticipated and loving recreation of a classic is now available (although limited due to high volume of pre-orders). Two-tone bucket hat, synonymous with Hampden trips in sunshine or under the floodlights.

We've tried to stay authentic to the original hats of the 80s and 90s. 

Perfect for fitba and festivals...

Designed in Aberdeen. Screen-printed by hand in Aberdeen. This hat IS Aberdeen.

This baseball cap is 100% cotton twill with flat peak.

Designed in Aberdeen. Embroidered in the UK. Standing Free all over Europe.

name: Aberdeen FC - European Song Bottle Opener
description:
... or is it a key ring. No it's a bottle opener. Hud on, it's a key ring!

Whatever you decide to use it for, the design used on the front of this is recognisable by Dons fans around the world. The white vinyl 'European Song' probably resides in thousands of AB postcode lofts.

Now you can own it, put it in your pocket (it's 58mm wide) and open bottles with it. No, put your keys on it. No, hud on open bottles with it...

name: Aberdeen FC - Glory in Gothenburg
description:
**LAST FEW REMAINING**

Final final batch, and back by popular demand.

We've been swamped by emails from disappointed Dandies that missed out the first time. Once these are gone, they really are gone...

'Glory in Gothenburg' commemorates the 30 year anniversary of Aberdeen FC winning their first European trophy.

This pewter statuette stands approximately 10cm tall and features an abstract depiction of Willie Miller's iconic one-handed celebration.

Designed in Aberdeen. Created by hand in Aberdeen. Born in Gothenburg.

Strictly limited in numbers.

name: Aberdeen FC - Come On You Reds Scarf
description:
Available for the first time. Aberdeen fans cup-tie banner design on a scarf.

We were commissioned to create a banner with the specific purpose to take to cup-ties. This banner has been all over Scotland but currently resides on the top tier of Richard Donald Stand.

The scarf is identical to the banner, on one side but on the other the colours are reversed. Funcy eh!? So whether Aberdeen FC are playing in home or away colours you're sorted...

Top quality thermal knitted jacquard scarves. Limited to FIFTY only. Every penny of profit will be donated to Red Army Fan Display Fund.

name: Aberdeen FC - East Coast Sweatshirt
description:
Fit Like - East Coast...

Our first sweat. 

Vintage typography on quality and soft AWDis sweatshirts.

name: Aberdeen FC - Accoste Tee
description:
An earlier Dolly design, revisited for Winter 2014.

A gentle parody of a famous brand, where the green crocodile logo is replaced by a humble red sheep.

A two-colour screen-print, on 'Bella + Canvas Athletic Grey' Tee.

It's meant for Aberdeen FC fans, but to be honest it's perfect for all sheep-botherers...

Designed in Aberdeen. Dispatched from Aberdeen.

name: Aberdeen FC - Dolly's XI
description:
The XI Greatest Aberdeen FC Players as voted for by you...

We've collaborated with Dons fans around the world in the creation of this Tee. The chosen XI is made up of the greatest Aberdeen FC footballers of all time.

Voted for by Aberdeen fans. Designed in Aberdeen. Screen printed by hand in Aberdeen. Dispatched from Aberdeen. This Tee IS Aberdeen.

name: Aberdeen FC - Legends and Cult Heroes: Niall McGinn
description:
The first installment of our 'Legends and Cult Heroes' series of Tees. Where better to start than Aberdeen FC Player of the Year - Niall McGinn?

We have collaborated with recent graduate of Gray's School of Art and Dons fan Gary Caldwell. For more info on Gary's work please check out www.garycaldwell.blogspot.co.uk.

He plays on the left. He plays on the riiight. Niall McGinn makes this his debut on a Dolly Tee (that needs work, I'm a designer not a poet).

Designed in Aberdeen, by Aberdeen fans and screen-printed by hand in Aberdeen.

name: Aberdeen FC - Legends and Cult Heroes: Eoin Jess
description:
The third, and final (for now) installment of our 'Legends and Cult Heroes' series of Tees. Where better to finish than Eoin Jess?

We have collaborated with recent graduate of Gray's School of Art and Dons fan Gary Caldwell. For more info on Gary's work please check out www.garycaldwell.blogspot.co.uk.

Designed in Aberdeen, by Aberdeen fans and screen-printed by hand in Aberdeen.

name: Aberdeen FC - Legends and Cult Heroes: Theo Snelders
description:
Second Installment 'Aberdeen FC - Legends and Cult Heroes'...

Signed from Twente Enschede, Theodorus Antonius Gerardus "Theo" Snelders made close to 300 appearances for Aberdeen FC. In his time at Pittodrie he was part of the cup double winning side of 1990, in 1988-89 he was the FA Players Player of the Year and was capped by Holland. 

Theo mysteriously vanished in 1996 but reappeared in Holland in 1999.

We have collaborated with recent graduate of Gray's School of Art and Dons fan Gary Caldwell to create this three colour print on Antique Cherry Red t-shirt. For more info on Gary's work please check out www.garycaldwell.blogspot.co.uk.

Designed in Aberdeen, by Aberdeen fans and screen-printed by hand in Aberdeen.

description:

It makes sense to combine the strength of Calvin Zola and the iconic strength of Bon Accord's Red Kola. 

Designed in Aberdeen. Screen printed by hand in Aberdeen. Born in the Democratic Republic of the Congo

name: Aberdeen FC - Flood
description:
This image celebrates Aberdeen FC midfielder, Willo Flood and his debut goal. We've seen him described as 'The New Barry Nicholson'. We think he's 'The New Gordon Strachan'. 

Three colour screen-print on the highest quality white Tee.

The original photography belongs to Scott Baxter. You can check some of his game photography at http://www.flickr.com/photos/scottbaxter or say hello on Twitter at @scottscb.

Designed in Aberdeen. Screen-printed by hand in Aberdeen. Dispatched from Aberdeen...

name: Aberdeen FC - Willie Miller Che Guevara Tee
description:
We were going to write some blurb about this design. About the iconic image and its absence for years. The fact we're using Richie's original design and using the same screen printer on the same high quality Tees. 

But all you need to know is, thanks to our collaboration with Dons supporting designer Richie, we are pleased to announce the iconic Che/Willie design is BACK!

name: Aberdeen FC - Stand Free 1983
description:
"Got. got, got, got, got, NEED!"

In celebration of Aberdeen FC's first trophy, the European Cup Winners Cup. Re-working of Panini's 1983 sticker album. High resolution, vinyl printing on heavy red cotton Tee.

Limited edition - there are no plans to re-stock once sold out signs go up.

This t-shirt is so authentic to the original Panini pages that goalscorer Eric Black isn't included.

Designed in Aberdeen. Printed in the UK. Swapped in playgrounds. But born in Gothenburg.

name: Aberdeen FC - Joey Tee
description:
Joey is BACK!

The second installment of our Limited Edition, Dolly Digital designed Tees. This Tee celebrates the 'King of the Beach End' - Joey Harper.

This t-shirt parodies the street artist Sheperd Fairey's OBEY project. These images of 'Andre the Giant', can bee seen all over the world. The 'Andre has a posse' slogan is synonymous with this design.

Well now, JOEY has a posse...

Designed in Aberdeen. Screen-printed by hand in Aberdeen. Born at the Beach End.

name: Aberdeen FC - Cupvinnar Cupen

Final Cupvinnar-Cupen

Onsdagen Den 11 Maj 1983 KL. 20.15

Ticket stub t-shirt, screen printed in red, from Ullevi Stadium on long-sleeved baseball style Tee. Small ECWC silhouette print on the back.

Designed in Aberdeen. Screen printed in Aberdeen. Born in Gothenburg.

name: Aberdeen FC - The Neil Simpson
description:
Wikipedia states: "Neil Alexander Simpson (born 15 November 1961 in London, England) is a former Scottish international footballer known for his time with Aberdeen F.C."

Dolly Digital shouts: "SIMMIE, SIMMY, SIMMIE, SIMMY..."

310 Appearances for Aberdeen FC.
31 Goals for Aberdeen FC.
Premier League x 2 
Scottish Cup x 3
Scottish League Cup x 1
European Cup Winners Cup x 1
Super Cup x 1

That's a major honour every 38.75 games.

This case celebrates Aberdeen FC winning the Super Cup. Defeating SV Hamburg, Aberdeen won the second major European trophy in their history. Still the only Scottish club to do this. Neil Simpson scored the crucial first goal at Pittodrie to ensure Aberdeen were crowned the number one team in Europe for 1983.

Please be aware that each case is individually made to order and we estimate 5 working days before you receive it.

Dolly Digital create unique, custom and personalised mobile phone cases using cutting edge thermal printing technology to offer cool phone cases that are a work of art.

We're bringing it up to date for the 2013-2014 season, and we're using it on mobile phone cases - a far cry from asking yer Ma to sew it onto yer tourie!

name: Aberdeen FC - Main Stand Missiles
description:
'Main Stand Missiles' features the warning that "Supporters carrying cans, bottles or missiles will not be admitted". Since the early 80's we have witnessed cans of Coke and bottles of Ribena being confiscated by over-zealous stewards and police. We've yet to witness a supporter carrying a missile...

Against Modern Football.

name: Aberdeen FC - Joey
description:
Joseph Montgomery Harper

The 'King' as he was affectionately christened by his beloved Beach End. Idolised at Pittodrie, 'goal a game Harper' achieved legendary status during his Pittodrie career that was broken by a spell with Everton and Hibs. Joey played in the Dons Cup winning sides of 1970 and 1976, and was still around as the Dons won the Premier in 1980. 

A parody of Shepard Fairey's OBEY street art campaign. Only this time JOEY has a posse...

name: Aitkens Bakery A2 Print
description:
The first from our home-grown, 'Iconic Doric' range of screen printed prints. Where better to start than a legendary image that defines 'Iconic Doric'... This image is recognisable to Aberdonian ex-pats and the home-bird alike. Features the memorable image that adorns the paper bag used to carry your bakery goods.

Screen printed by hand in Aberdeen on A2 160gsm paper. 

These are restricted to a limited run of 25.

Dolly Digital says: "2 weel-fired rowies w’jam… Affa affa fine…"

Wikipedia says: "A buttery, also known as a rowie, rollie, Aberdeen roll is a savory Scottish bread roll. 

They are noted for their flaky texture and buttery taste (hence the name), similar to a flattened, round croissant, with a very salty taste. They are often eaten toasted with jam or butter, although the high fat content makes them extremely hot when toasted. The fat content is partly lard. In practice commercial production uses vegetable oils instead of butter."
